Class FingerEvent<T extends PircBotX>

java.lang.Object

      org.pircbotx.hooks.events.FingerEvent<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
GenericCTCPCommand<T>, GenericEvent<T>
public class FingerEvent<T extends PircBotX>
extends Event<T>
implements GenericCTCPCommand<T>

This event is dispatched whenever we receive a FINGER request.

CoreHooks automatically responds correctly. Unless CoreHooks is removed from the bot's ListenerManager, Listeners of this event should not send a response as the user will get two responses

Author:
Leon Blakey
